<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870603-0037 </DOCNO><HL> Investor Branch Lifts StakeIn BancTexas Group Inc.</HL><DD> 06/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BTXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ben S. Branch said he holds a 5.9% stake in BancTexas Group Inc.'s Class A cumulative convertible preferred stock outstanding, and may seek a more active role in company affairs.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the Amherst, Mass., investor said he holds 52,025 BancTexas Class A preferred shares, including 23,600 shares purchased from May 8 to May 26 at prices ranging from $1.375 to $3.125 a share.    In another filing, Mr. Branch increased his stake to 7.4% of the Dallas-based bank holding company's 1.4625 cumulative convertible preferred stock outstanding. Mr. Branch said he holds 45,340 BancTexas 1.4625 preferred shares, including 15,040 shares purchased from March 24 to May 18 at prices ranging from $3 to $4.25 a share.    In both filings, Mr. Branch said he holds his BancTexas shares for investment purposes, but reserves the right to play a more active role in BancTexas &quot;if the opportunity arises and appears advantageous.&quot;    BancTexas officials hadn't any comment on the filings. </TEXT></DOC>